<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-52-1094 </DOCNO><TEXT>The four major mining accidents in South African mines since 1983 werecaused by explosion, even though this type of accident normally accountsfor only a very small percentage of total fatalities and injuries. Pressurebursts and falls of ground, as well as transport accidents, are the majorcauses of fatalities and injuries.</TEXT></DOC>